The defendant Cullen K Tippery was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Cullen K Tippery is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Cullen K Tippery was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Cases called: 16CF332, 16CF338, 15CM671, Defendant Cullen K Tippery in court with attorney Wm. Ginsberg.  Crystal N Long appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant previously plead to count in 15CM671, sentencing today. Court went over the rights & elements in the two felony cases. Defendant pled guilty to counts 2 in 16CF338 & 16CF332. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment. Argument for expungement of count 2 in 16CF332 by Atty. Ginsberg, defendant and his mother. ADA Long opposed expungement. Court withheld sentence, 2 years probation in all 3 cases. Conditions: Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Submit DNA sample. Costs in 16CF338 are $443, in 16CF332 are $453, in 15CM671 are $443. Cases are concurrent with each other, but consecutive to any other probation.  All remaining counts read in and dismissed. Court denied defense's motion for expungement.  Stipulation to be filed on jail credit by Jan. 31, 2017.
Plea/sentencing hearing on January 24, 2017 at 01:00 pm.
